Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["The Stabilizer Formalism By Computation", "Title",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9912547710704803`*^9, 3.991254781624619*^9}},
 CellID->1214104153,ExpressionUUID->"d3f28ff3-6a4e-4879-8286-abe73761dc7e"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This document teaches the stabilizer formalism the way one would teach it \
at a chalkboard with a kernel open: every claim is immediately computed. We \
start from the observation that a single qubit can be specified not by its \
two amplitudes but by the one operator that fixes it, build that idea into \
the Aaronson-Gottesman tableau, and ride it all the way to thousand-qubit \
Clifford circuits, error-correcting codes, graph states, magic states, and \
Clifford channels. We close with a measured, honest comparison against the \
specialized C++ and Julia stabilizer simulators. The arc is: a state is what \
stabilizes it (single qubit), ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["n", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c467ae7b-32ad-454f-ac4a-9f4631830b78"],
 " generators replace ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["2", 
   StyleBox["n", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "5e991103-0da0-4b57-95d9-aaf028555c72"],
 " amplitudes (the tableau), entanglement and measurement become linear \
algebra over ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox["\|01d53d", "2"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "b0ccfa78-f7a4-4f26-bd97-2597c9001e71"],
 " (the field of two elements ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", "0"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"1", "}"}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "8ab6f0db-cb7a-481b-87ce-33fbccdc6aa9"],
 " with all arithmetic done mod 2, so that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"1", "+", "1", "=", "0"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d5ac30d4-be96-4807-bbf3-fd1a9ba7c94f"],
 " and vector addition is the bitwise XOR), and then scale, codes, and the \
frontier. The audience is graduate students who know quantum mechanics and \
the Pauli group but have not yet seen why a stabilizer state of a thousand \
qubits is something you can hold in your hand. Every construction in this \
document is built explicitly so you can change it, break it, and extend it. \
The ",
 ButtonBox["Wolfram QuantumFramework",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://resources.wolframcloud.com/PacletRepository/resources/\
Wolfram/QuantumFramework/"], None}],
 " symbols we exercise live in the ",
 ButtonBox["Wolfram QuantumFramework",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://resources.wolframcloud.com/PacletRepository/resources/\
Wolfram/QuantumFramework/"], None}],
 " paclet; the central one is PauliStabilizer."
}], "Abstract",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.991254697722966*^9, 
  3.991254715313615*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"03a156da-d146-4aca-ac8d-\
43fb23254601"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Setup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"fa44b638-4b1a-4eb8-8640-8a855115ae38"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We load the framework from the working tree so the fast paths and recent \
fixes are present. On a current release, the plain ",
 Cell[BoxData["Needs"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "ce7211d0-334b-4357-8598-bd74d5f11356"],
 " line alone suffices."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"5171869f-a087-4b08-8a2b-e104c12bc40a"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"PacletInstall", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<https://www.wolfr.am/DevWQCF\>\"", ",", 
    RowBox[{"ForceVersionInstall", "->", "True"}]}], "]"}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"Needs", "[", "\"\<Wolfram`QuantumFramework`\>\"", "]"}]}], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.991254667654751*^9, 
  3.991254669777563*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c0572ef5-ba29-43cd-b4f8-\
33538b13afc0"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["The core functions at a glance", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"ffe02b3c-d985-4358-9421-cc1011c6a0ac"],

Cell["\<\
Before the narrative, the whole working surface, grouped by task. Every call \
is exercised in context where it is introduced; this is the map.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"dd916ca6-8ebf-48b0-b0fa-6a86553e17bb"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Construct", "TI"],
 " a register, from signed Pauli strings, a named code, or a random Clifford: \
",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", "n", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "591ab817-c309-4aeb-99c3-8f3f05fccfe4"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"\"\<XX\>\"", ",", " ", "\"\<ZZ\>\""}], "}"}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "980f6712-29db-42f0-9d59-04f9bdce2fb3"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", "\"\<SteaneCode\>\"", "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "604ee98c-7fc1-42e0-a6fa-67c887e00737"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<Random\>\"", "[", "n", "]"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "b1caa34e-0604-4275-99e2-896978edb870"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"b97f723c-3356-4b86-bdd1-31d8a1c57285"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Apply a Clifford gate", "TI"],
 " one at a time: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<H\>\"", ",", " ", "j"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c11a1d73-040e-4f41-a6e3-8ea05dd17664"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<S\>\"", ",", " ", "j"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "4a4e9c57-a764-4530-bbe9-cecd359b45fc"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<CNOT\>\"", ",", " ", "j", ",", " ", "k"}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a1c84429-86d0-4fe3-8409-9fb928d1d36f"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<CZ\>\"", ",", " ", "j", ",", " ", "k"}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "b21a3eaa-43a8-4849-bd88-89386159b6fb"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<SWAP\>\"", ",", " ", "j", ",", " ", "k"}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "4b1abf8f-5471-49fc-89a0-75f979b9eae0"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"69436816-2c05-467d-81c1-ec1e51101771"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Apply a whole circuit", "TI"],
 " as a gate list, routed through the compiled engine (bare names take \
default targets, ",
 Cell[BoxData["->"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "735107ec-d2ba-46fc-8aee-858a8a780891"],
 " sets explicit ones): ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"\"\<H\>\"", ",", " ", "\"\<CNOT\>\"", ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"\"\<CNOT\>\"", " ", "->", " ", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"2", ",", " ", "3"}], "}"}]}]}], "}"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "371cf782-3fdd-4993-a208-1c7eb15d078b"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"bdd52fe9-9678-4746-bc51-9dc2ddbc2bf2"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Inspect", "TI"],
 ": ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", "\"\<Stabilizers\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "fdaecced-d857-4c4d-9fc4-6ff4afe0eafe"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", "\"\<Tableau\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f30275b7-3c08-4ad5-80f4-3e908a2b67af"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", "\"\<Matrix\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d00edb99-65da-429d-ba42-877c65045966"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", "\"\<State\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "13921df8-68b0-4c3d-9c33-79591b430adc"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"fb5d715b-f2db-4072-a5e6-459a1d77538a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Measure", "TI"],
 ": ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<M\>\"", ",", " ", "q"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "92fcd54a-c8a4-4a2d-b9f7-d2a903033d30"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<M\>\"", ",", " ", "\"\<ZZ\>\""}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "5a9e0f76-cab9-431d-bb46-bcc144e5676a"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<Expectation\>\"", ",", " ", "\"\<ZZ\>\""}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "fb214ae4-b3de-4015-8500-5cc52db0b17c"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<SymbolicMeasure\>\"", ",", " ", "q"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a073237c-f892-4251-9708-79559997cb3a"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"cdd23c1b-8b5b-4bee-ba4c-72293494928e"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Entanglement entropy", "TI"],
 " across a cut: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<Entropy\>\"", ",", " ", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"1", ",", " ", "2"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f351022e-75a1-4449-a93d-d6b5ff499dc1"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"359ca9a8-64e4-4888-8381-0b42e198750e"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Sibling heads", "TI"],
 ": ",
 Cell[BoxData["StabilizerFrame"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "4a3cc3be-1c16-43ed-ae84-e278b6c3174d"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData["CliffordChannel"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "9ba3bd50-8854-4c39-b012-26adf00edada"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData["GraphState"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "e13882c9-2d73-4e0d-ada0-6e4260e6c22c"],
 " with ",
 Cell[BoxData["LocalComplement"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "e1c2127d-90ab-4645-953a-bff852d8154d"],
 ", and the predicate ",
 Cell[BoxData["StabilizerStateQ"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "536a24cb-91ce-432d-8532-80bcded1177c"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"a4f610f9-39ad-4e9f-95e0-3c7f268d0005"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Why stabilizers: the exponential wall", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"c7afc77c-cb8d-4ad7-9287-f25d7c71ff23"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A pure state of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["n", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "111e19b1-da0a-44a6-bc26-1c16371a13f8"],
 " qubits is a unit vector in ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["\:2102", 
   SuperscriptBox["2", 
    StyleBox["n", "TI"]]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "1ce9f18b-c029-4eed-b18b-2757f43382eb"],
 ", so writing it down means storing ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["2", 
   StyleBox["n", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "dd3755b5-df43-4c1d-b12c-04cc1541d552"],
 " complex amplitudes. At ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["n", "TI"], "=", "20"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f47400a2-f76c-4e61-9ca1-f586c76c4a42"],
 " that is already a million numbers; at ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["n", "TI"], "=", "50"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "8477d1ad-c65f-4476-81b4-4430cd55259c"],
 " it is about ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["10", "15"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c9e34853-38dd-4054-9ef4-f1d92c390d6a"],
 ", a petabyte of amplitudes even at one byte each; by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["n", "TI"], "=", "100"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "3ec6745a-8544-44bc-b30f-5d54e071ed72"],
 " it passes the number of atoms in a building (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[Tilde]", 
   SuperscriptBox["10", "30"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "eb4032ad-019d-4e14-a760-2c9a4841571d"],
 "). Yet many of the states we care most about, including every state any \
error-correcting code protects, are not generic: they sit at the fixed points \
of a large group of Pauli operators, and that structure can be stored in ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["O", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["n", "TI"], "2"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "4cfce94f-d5f5-4129-8909-6cfe4e01be53"],
 " bits."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"95a3cab2-ad0f-40a6-a7ab-d2a1080b8e3f"],

Cell["\<\
To feel the wall, ask for the dense state vector of a 20-qubit GHZ state and \
look only at its length:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"4864748d-2130-45cf-8a97-f32baf0fcb4a"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Length", " ", "@", " ", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", 
    RowBox[{"\"\<GHZ\>\"", "[", "20", "]"}], "]"}], "[", "\"\<StateVector\>\"",
    "]"}]}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[2]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"c6cd0996-a192-4c9f-abc4-70e68a505c01"],

Cell[BoxData["1048576"], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[2]= ",ExpressionUUID->"a98239e8-3a90-42e1-85cd-d5409bb7f1c4"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "That is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["2", "20"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "1b8a2221-46bc-4338-9fa4-66caf1216629"],
 " amplitudes for a state that is pinned down completely by 20 short Pauli \
strings. The stabilizer formalism is the bookkeeping that exploits exactly \
this gap."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"534a4f05-d2aa-49b5-b573-e9fbbd02c23f"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["A state is what fixes it: the single qubit", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"0eda7270-8a92-48e7-8a5b-cb93810cb78d"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The central move is to stop describing a state by its amplitudes and start \
describing it by the operators that leave it invariant. The state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "8adbaf7f-3239-4bd0-81f1-192d8047749b"],
 " is the unique ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"+", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "3ac30087-37e5-4915-9aef-5e36e464da78"],
 " eigenvector of the Pauli operator ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "60bafbde-fd2e-482c-bda5-3cdad7025273"],
 ". We say ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "dd688986-c999-4a70-a114-74adf91039aa"],
 " ",
 StyleBox["stabilizes", "TI"],
 " ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "272d680b-7755-4b28-81c8-dbc17feed7e2"],
 ", and since one operator already determines a one-qubit state up to \
normalization, that single fact ",
 StyleBox["is", "TI"],
 " the state."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"9668f03f-7ae5-4009-ab71-4a075a2dc8e6"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A caution that defines the whole subject: this works only for special \
states. Of all one-qubit pure states, exactly six are ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"+", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a858ff94-6bee-4caf-9ef7-ad255ed5e9ab"],
 " eigenstates of a Pauli: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "0d9e5f4b-17e6-4913-8b23-03eba0899c1e"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"1"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "328f93d1-f5c9-4c9b-87ec-1f648925cbfd"],
 " for ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[PlusMinus]", 
   StyleBox["Z", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "556e1d82-6d15-469b-8ef4-a3ce4e017161"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"\[PlusMinus]"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "996a7251-be46-4dfc-8adb-42de3be1be28"],
 " for ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[PlusMinus]", 
   StyleBox["X", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "116e9e6b-4eb7-4420-9d6b-df2e4f52a911"],
 ", and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    StyleBox["i", "TI"]},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "71dc3a1d-ea51-479c-8d94-4252077140ae"],
 " for ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[PlusMinus]", 
   StyleBox["Y", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "14140511-da71-478c-9b76-345d8fc84a60"],
 ". These six are the ",
 StyleBox["stabilizer states", "TI"],
 ", and the formalism is exactly their theory and its multi-qubit \
generalization; a generic ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["cos",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], 
    StyleBox["\[Theta]", "TI"], 
    TemplateBox[{"0"},
     "Ket"]}], "+", 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["sin",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], 
    StyleBox["\[Theta]", "TI"], 
    TemplateBox[{"1"},
     "Ket"]}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "8cc79afd-0aa7-49a3-8b07-9b7dd3b87efd"],
 " is fixed by no Pauli and falls outside it. What makes the restriction \
worth a whole subject is that the states it does cover are exactly the ones \
error correction and large parts of quantum algorithms are built from."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"43ae7e98-7d7f-4c4c-a0d6-87d9a59cf856"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This deserves a closer look, because \"fixed by no Pauli\" is not the same \
as \"fixed by nothing.\" ",
 StyleBox["Every", "TI"],
 " pure state is the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"+", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "be792e4c-c64a-405a-a686-a6c27d0712b1"],
 " eigenstate of some operator. The reflection ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"2", 
    TemplateBox[{
      StyleBox["\[Psi]", "TI"]},
     "Ket"], 
    TemplateBox[{
      StyleBox["\[Psi]", "TI"]},
     "Bra"]}], "-", 
   StyleBox["I", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "e3d80fd9-ae8d-491f-acde-e598da4c24af"],
 " does the job for any ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    StyleBox["\[Psi]", "TI"]},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "be98545d-ce8f-4d29-9957-f1eabf04ac2b"],
 " at all, leaving ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    StyleBox["\[Psi]", "TI"]},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "856a75df-014e-4efb-a05f-44fec6f61f76"],
 " alone and flipping the sign of everything orthogonal to it:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"83a30814-97a5-42e4-bc9d-790c859c9570"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"psi", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"Cos", "[", 
      RowBox[{"1", "/", "3"}], "]"}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
      RowBox[{"1", "/", "3"}], "]"}]}], "}"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"reflection", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"2", " ", 
     RowBox[{"Outer", "[", 
      RowBox[{"Times", ",", " ", "psi", ",", " ", "psi"}], "]"}]}], " ", "-", 
    " ", 
    RowBox[{"IdentityMatrix", "[", "2", "]"}]}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Simplify", "[", 
   RowBox[{"reflection", " ", ".", " ", "psi"}], "]"}], " ", "==", " ", 
  "psi"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[3]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"21f5c0ff-5062-465a-b2f3-978d69f93be7"],

Cell[BoxData["True"], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[3]= ",ExpressionUUID->"2306d4b2-4f76-4f43-b44b-8e377bdb4303"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["\<\
That stabilizing operator is a dense, structureless thing that turns \
continuously as the state turns:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c054fc22-052e-4570-80f2-6a0279c1aa62"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Simplify", "[", "reflection", "]"}], " ", "//", " ", 
  "MatrixForm"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[4]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"e07bb462-81fd-4139-805c-4cb4ed6acba3"],

Cell[BoxData[
 TagBox[
  RowBox[{"(", "\[NoBreak]", GridBox[{
     {
      RowBox[{"Cos", "[", 
       FractionBox["2", "3"], "]"}], 
      RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
       FractionBox["2", "3"], "]"}]},
     {
      RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
       FractionBox["2", "3"], "]"}], 
      RowBox[{"-", 
       RowBox[{"Cos", "[", 
        FractionBox["2", "3"], "]"}]}]}
    },
    GridBoxAlignment->{"Columns" -> {{Center}}, "Rows" -> {{Baseline}}},
    GridBoxSpacings->{"Columns" -> {
        Offset[0.27999999999999997`], {
         Offset[0.7]}, 
        Offset[0.27999999999999997`]}, "Rows" -> {
        Offset[0.2], {
         Offset[0.4]}, 
        Offset[0.2]}}], "\[NoBreak]", ")"}],
  Function[BoxForm`e$, 
   MatrixForm[BoxForm`e$]]]], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[4]= ",ExpressionUUID->"ec4a1750-21e3-407c-bf4f-e917db1d3012"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "So \"a state is what fixes it\" is, on its own, vacuous: this reflection \
takes the full ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["2", 
   StyleBox["n", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a9b3a191-ce28-42ad-8c72-2bcd6964cde5"],
 " amplitudes to write down, exactly the cost we are fleeing, and a gate \
turns it into some other arbitrary operator. The power comes entirely from \
restricting the fixing operators to the ",
 StyleBox["Pauli group", "TI"],
 ", which is special on four counts that only pay off together:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"8e6f5ebe-4be8-4d3d-bee3-2bd4c84da952"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Cheap to name", "TI"],
 ": a Pauli string is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["O", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   StyleBox["n", "TI"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a6f85151-595d-4400-a49f-db6be70f14cd"],
 " bits, two per qubit and a sign, not ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["2", 
   StyleBox["n", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "83359e42-6eb5-4419-9a70-39751f56166b"],
 " amplitudes."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"4094bfa3-da4d-4880-85bd-10acbf75e82a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Clean spectrum", "TI"],
 ": it squares to the identity, so its eigenvalues are ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[PlusMinus]", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "5d2c9969-6f19-484a-84f1-0ee362220963"],
 ", and \"fixed by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["P", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "47c9e367-5205-49ea-8d92-a1bf09507b99"],
 "\" sharpens to the binary fact \"",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"+", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "17adb6ac-a017-4e9c-84af-9e29423b2396"],
 " eigenstate.\""
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"d9832576-8ac6-4817-8299-80b1da38d591"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Commute or anticommute", "TI"],
 ": any two Paulis do one or the other, with nothing in between, so ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["n", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d6d2f77a-a203-48e5-96bd-8e5e70fbf8a3"],
 " independent commuting Paulis halve the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["2", 
   StyleBox["n", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "5a3541b7-8cb1-40cb-a391-961a73f9c0b8"],
 "-dimensional space ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["n", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "bf8cd6fc-c97a-4aea-a7dc-54204bafb2d1"],
 " times and leave a unique joint ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"+", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "837fd58e-3e8f-4904-9b4d-7506099facdb"],
 " eigenstate, which is why a list of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["n", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "b7160452-cc4c-4230-addc-47de0940ae66"],
 " generators pins down one state exactly."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"e0bbf4a0-7f09-4bc7-8cb4-7bed1676fec4"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Closed under Clifford gates", "TI"],
 ": conjugation by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["H", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "97c9c622-bcb6-4e50-9135-e3fdfa2d28f4"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["S", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d0ebebd8-aac6-4212-bf49-bf4ba2bb51c3"],
 ", and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["CNOT",
   FontSlant->"Plain"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "7b54e4ee-6a7d-4efe-b8ca-8dfd1a660671"],
 " sends Paulis to Paulis, so the description never leaves the Pauli language \
as the state evolves."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"093ace38-4ab2-4493-a659-67ba59cce403"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The reflection ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"2", 
    TemplateBox[{
      StyleBox["\[Psi]", "TI"]},
     "Ket"], 
    TemplateBox[{
      StyleBox["\[Psi]", "TI"]},
     "Bra"]}], "-", 
   StyleBox["I", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "fac5e34e-d033-4eb8-9a05-be2328de9f25"],
 " has none of these properties. Drop any one of them and naming a state by \
what fixes it stops paying its way; keep all four and it becomes the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["O", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["n", "TI"], "2"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "cc7f8136-167a-4c62-a741-21cf3fcd9c07"],
 " tableau the rest of this document runs on."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"4c4e5027-7d08-453f-bf5e-763c187406c2"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Verify that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "78b4dedc-d762-447b-8f43-0199fdd1cdf6"],
 " fixes ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "9756fcc7-dbf9-437c-88cc-2bb0eac84a00"],
 ", recalling that the built-in ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliMatrix", "[", "1", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f88472fb-721e-4852-bf94-ce944ac7bcda"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliMatrix", "[", "2", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f9366a8f-97e4-4670-9e8a-d02989c07693"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliMatrix", "[", "3", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "8908ddae-1df8-4b34-b43c-e5d8e4a0d366"],
 " are ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["X", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "0381c3aa-03d3-40b0-83fe-d3c130c89b39"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Y", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "473f0173-deec-4d49-8f04-a783c045de8c"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "37c19d7f-ac3a-4be0-b96b-123ecc2bf00f"],
 ":"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"434c4543-73c1-4a6d-9ba5-94db2a0501bf"],

