Cell["What we have established:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b321d0ea-b892-47c5-ac4a-9dfc5f0c6392"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "An entangled stabilizer state is one whose generators are multi-qubit Pauli \
strings; Bell is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["\[LeftAngleBracket]",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox[
     RowBox[{"X", "X"}], "TI"], ",", 
    StyleBox[
     RowBox[{"Z", "Z"}], "TI"]}], "\[VeryThinSpace]", 
   StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "522307f7-d6f1-4767-a4a1-6ad787123028"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"57bf6d62-c6ce-4bb9-b777-3ff816a86441"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Entanglement entropy is an ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox["\|01d53d", "2"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "ca6ffa25-f8de-4e21-a05f-88fe2ba3ecf4"],
 " rank, computable at ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["n", "TI"], "=", "1000"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d44fa461-4cf9-410c-8ad2-98ec5b8a3267"],
 " in milliseconds."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"5597fabd-9f0c-40ef-bf63-30244d39ad07"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The cost of all this is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["O", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["n", "TI"], "2"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "bcf3c846-86cc-4940-838d-0acd22a874ad"],
 " storage and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["O", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["n", "TI"], "3"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "9d10a003-61e8-44af-be66-3468984b41cc"],
 " for the rank, never ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["O", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   SuperscriptBox["2", 
    StyleBox["n", "TI"]], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "923e1eec-87e9-436c-a8fa-2fafa44773d7"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"18f0513a-d000-4809-a20c-df53486a69fe"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Measurement: randomness, back-action, and correlation", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"21d91f99-46a9-4626-bf34-a935fde69756"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Measurement is where the destabilizers earn their keep. Measuring ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a334774e-2ac4-4411-a4c8-658bc49e4187"],
 " on qubit ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["a", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "60b1d93e-7eca-402f-94f7-0b226073acaf"],
 " splits into two cases. If ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["Z", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["a", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "44a56bc6-5db9-445e-abf2-a6d9f946d3fe"],
 " commutes with every stabilizer, then ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[PlusMinus]", 
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["Z", "TI"], 
    StyleBox["a", "TI"]]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "4717110e-fbb2-403c-ac6f-5093a381ed7a"],
 " already lies in the stabilizer group: the outcome is ",
 StyleBox["deterministic", "TI"],
 ", the state is unchanged, and the bit is the sign of the generator product \
that equals ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["Z", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["a", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a1696ccd-2d8d-4676-a19b-221d794efa2e"],
 ", which the destabilizers locate in ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["O", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["n", "TI"], "2"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "6141e442-73b4-4b79-a3fd-be245fd58095"],
 ". If instead some stabilizer anticommutes with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["Z", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["a", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f43268f1-88c1-4520-98e3-fba62c0e5f99"],
 ", the outcome is a fair coin, and the post-measurement state follows from a \
sequence of Aaronson-Gottesman row sums into one anticommuting generator, \
with a destabilizer as scratch. Either way the work is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["O", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["n", "TI"], "2"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a6bde160-5bb8-4430-ac35-19cf4b5c9169"],
 ", never ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["O", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   SuperscriptBox["2", 
    StyleBox["n", "TI"]], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f20545a1-3703-487f-a80f-a409d144c590"],
 "."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"02f11242-40c1-4500-bbee-e816a7a1a23d"],

Cell["\<\
A measurement on a stabilizer state returns an association from outcome to \
post-state. For the Bell state, measuring qubit 1 is random, so both branches \
appear:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"4dd72482-404d-4d78-b318-b4fae624b10d"],

